foreach ($costumes as $costumeData) { $sizes = $costumeData['sizes']; $images = $costumeData['images']; unset($costumeData['sizes'], $costumeData['images']);
// Create costume $costume = Costume::create($costumeData);
// Create sizes foreach ($sizes as $sizeData) { Size::create([ 'costume_id' => $costume->id, 'size_label' => $sizeData['size_label'], 'quantity_available' => $sizeData['quantity_available'], ]); }
// Create images foreach ($images as $imageUrl) { CostumeImage::create([ 'costume_id' => $costume->id, 'image_url' => $imageUrl, ]); } }
$this->command->info('✅ Created ' . count($costumes) . ' costumes with sizes and images'); } } ```
### Step 3: Run the Seeder
```bash cd backend php artisan db:seed --class=CostumeSeeder ```
### Step 4: Restart Backend
```bash php artisan serve ```
### Step 5: Test the API
Open browser or use curl: ``` http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/costumes/1 ```
You should see complete data with: - ✅ name, slug, brand - ✅ description - ✅ price_per_day (not 0) - ✅ featured_image_url - ✅ available: true - ✅ sizes array with quantities - ✅ images array
### Step 6: Rebuild Android App
```bash gradlew.bat clean assembleDebug ```
### Step 7: Run App Again
The costume details should now display correctly!
## Expected Result
After fix, you should see: - ✅ Image loads - ✅ Name: "Costume Slim-Fit Noir" - ✅ Brand: "Maison Élégance" - ✅ Price: "49,99 MAD / jour" - ✅ Description: Full text - ✅ Availability: "Disponible" (green) - ✅ Sizes: S (2), M (5), L (3), XL (1) - ✅ "Louer Maintenant" button enabled
## Verification
Check Android Studio Logcat for: ``` D/CostumeDetail: Loading costume ID: 1 D/CostumeDetail: Response code: 200 D/CostumeDetail: Costume loaded: Costume Slim-Fit Noir D/CostumeDetail: Price: 49.99 D/CostumeDetail: Available: true D/CostumeDetail: Sizes count: 4 ```
## Still Not Working?
1. Check backend logs: `tail -f backend/storage/logs/laravel.log` 2. Verify database: `php artisan tinker` then `Costume::with('sizes')->first()` 3. Check network in Logcat: Filter "OkHttp" 4. Verify BASE_URL in RetrofitClient.java: `http://10.0.2.2:8000/api/`

